WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:27.960
In the Frame, by Polly Sweetman. It is the end of Lisa and Alice's holiday.

00:27.960 --> 00:31.200
They are leaving the Hotel Oracle.

00:31.200 --> 00:34.120
They are leaving Greece.

00:34.120 --> 00:36.920
They are going to the airport.

00:36.920 --> 00:41.280
They are going home.

00:41.280 --> 00:43.200
Goodbye, Kostas!

00:43.200 --> 00:45.160
Goodbye, Eleni!

00:45.160 --> 00:47.840
Thank you for our wonderful holiday!

00:47.840 --> 00:55.920
Come back to this island next year!

00:55.920 --> 00:59.680
Lisa and Alice are on the airport bus.

00:59.680 --> 01:03.840
The bus is stopping at another hotel.

01:03.840 --> 01:06.920
Some people are outside the hotel.

01:06.920 --> 01:13.520
They are going to the airport too.

01:13.520 --> 01:16.080
Look at that poor woman!

01:16.080 --> 01:19.400
She has two small children.

01:19.400 --> 01:22.200
She has a lot of luggage.

01:22.200 --> 01:24.480
And she has a pushchair.

01:24.480 --> 01:27.760
Let's help her.

01:27.760 --> 01:31.920
Lisa and Alice help the woman with her luggage.

01:31.920 --> 01:34.640
They help her with the pushchair.

01:34.640 --> 01:43.920
They help her with her children.

01:43.920 --> 01:48.440
I'm Lisa and this is my friend, Alice.

01:48.440 --> 01:50.160
Thank you, Lisa.

01:50.160 --> 01:51.800
Thank you, Alice.

01:51.800 --> 01:54.400
My name is Vera Brown.

01:54.400 --> 02:03.960
My children's names are Peter and Helen.

02:03.960 --> 02:06.360
I'm very worried.

02:06.360 --> 02:08.680
My husband is ill.

02:08.680 --> 02:10.680
He is in England.

02:10.680 --> 02:12.800
I must go to him.

02:12.800 --> 02:14.800
I'm going home.

02:14.800 --> 02:16.920
That's very sad news.

02:16.920 --> 02:19.680
I'm sorry, Vera.

02:19.680 --> 02:22.360
We're going to England too.

02:22.360 --> 02:25.680
We'll help you.

02:25.680 --> 02:28.920
Lisa and Alice are on the plane.

02:28.920 --> 02:31.680
Vera is on the plane too.

02:31.680 --> 02:35.320
She is sitting with her children.

02:35.320 --> 02:37.600
Look at this newspaper.

02:37.600 --> 02:40.840
Do you remember this painting?

02:40.840 --> 02:42.480
Yes.

02:42.480 --> 02:46.560
It's a painting from the island's museum!

02:46.560 --> 02:49.600
The artist is French.

02:49.600 --> 02:52.920
He's a famous French painter.

02:56.400 --> 03:01.520
The passengers are leaving the plane.

03:01.520 --> 03:04.560
Here we are in England, Vera.

03:04.560 --> 03:06.720
We'll help you at the airport.

03:06.720 --> 03:08.120
Thank you.

03:08.120 --> 03:12.080
You are very kind.

03:12.080 --> 03:16.600
Lisa, Alice and Vera are in the airport.

03:16.600 --> 03:19.840
Alice is getting their luggage.

03:23.320 --> 03:25.760
This is our last bag.

03:25.760 --> 03:28.320
Now we have everything.

03:28.320 --> 03:31.120
Now we must go to Customs.

03:31.120 --> 03:36.440
Please, I must go to the toilet!

03:36.440 --> 03:41.080
Vera is taking Peter to the toilet.

03:41.080 --> 03:42.720
Don't worry, Vera.

03:42.720 --> 03:44.520
I'll stay here.

03:44.520 --> 03:46.480
I'll stay with your luggage.

03:46.480 --> 03:49.360
Oh, thank you, Alice!

03:49.360 --> 03:53.720
Lisa, please go through Customs with Helen.

03:53.720 --> 03:56.400
Wait for Alice and me in the cafe.

03:56.400 --> 03:58.800
OK.

03:58.800 --> 04:01.200
Vera is at Customs.

04:01.200 --> 04:05.280
A customs officer is searching her luggage.

04:05.280 --> 04:09.160
Alice hears two customs officers talking.

04:09.160 --> 04:10.080
She is surprised.

04:14.040 --> 04:16.400
That is Vera Brownlow.

04:16.400 --> 04:18.360
She's an art thief!

04:18.360 --> 04:20.600
She steals paintings.

04:20.600 --> 04:22.080
Yes.

04:22.080 --> 04:25.920
But there are no paintings in her luggage.

04:25.920 --> 04:31.440
Oh! A painting is missing from the island's museum.

04:31.440 --> 04:34.160
And Vera is a thief!

04:34.160 --> 04:36.200
I must talk to these men.

04:43.480 --> 04:46.160
There's Alice!

04:46.160 --> 04:49.240
But where is Vera?

04:49.240 --> 04:51.920
Is she all right?

04:51.920 --> 04:53.200
Is Peter all right?

04:56.120 --> 04:58.920
Vera comes into the cafe.

04:58.920 --> 05:02.800
She is holding Peter's hand.

05:02.800 --> 05:04.680
Here we are at last!

05:04.680 --> 05:09.120
The customs officers are searching many travellers today.

05:09.120 --> 05:12.120
I'll take Helen and the pushchair now.

05:12.120 --> 05:14.480
My sister is going to meet me.

05:14.480 --> 05:18.280
She will help me with my luggage.

05:18.280 --> 05:20.880
Suddenly, there are customs officers

05:20.880 --> 05:24.320
and police officers in the cafe.

05:24.320 --> 05:28.040
One officer is searching the pushchair.

05:28.040 --> 05:31.000
He is looking in the frame.

05:31.000 --> 05:33.080
What is happening?

05:33.080 --> 05:36.840
Lisa, these are not Vera's children.

05:36.840 --> 05:39.600
They are her sister's children.

05:39.600 --> 05:42.760
Vera is an art thief.

05:42.760 --> 05:45.960
Do you remember the island's museum?

05:45.960 --> 05:49.360
Do you remember the stolen painting?

05:49.360 --> 05:53.560
The customs officers are looking for the stolen painting.

05:57.120 --> 06:01.360
The customs officers have the stolen painting.

06:01.360 --> 06:04.320
They are very pleased.

06:04.320 --> 06:07.240
Vera's sister has her children.

06:07.240 --> 06:10.240
She is very pleased, too.

06:10.240 --> 06:12.840
Well done, Lisa and Alice!

06:12.840 --> 06:15.760
There is a big reward for this painting.

06:15.760 --> 06:17.600
You'll get the money.

06:17.600 --> 06:19.440
That's great!

06:19.440 --> 06:23.080
We'll go on another holiday next year.

06:23.080 --> 06:24.560
LAUGHTER
